        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec 18 1868</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thank you for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> letter of Dec 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> &amp; for your great kindness in informing me about the development of the spurs in the 2 species of Pavo.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> If in the course of the winter or spring you sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> perceive any difference in their rate of development, I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> esteem it a <hi rend="underline">singular</hi> favour if you wd inform me, as I have no other means of ascertaining the point.</p>
<p>With sincere thanks &amp; respect | I remain dear Sir | yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
